To set the `temperature` and `topP` parameters when creating a code interpreter agent in TypeScript, include them in the `completionArgs` object as shown in the example:

```typescript
const codeAgent = await client.beta.agents.create({
    model: "mistral-medium-latest", // or another model like "mistral-medium-2505"
    name: "Coding Agent",
    instructions: "Use the code interpreter tool when you have to run code.",
    description: "Agent used to execute code using the interpreter tool.",
    tools: [{ type: "code_interpreter" }],
    completionArgs: {
        temperature: 0.3,  // Set temperature here
        topP: 0.95,        // Set topP here
    }
});
```

This is documented in **[1]** (Code Interpreter, TypeScript example). The same parameters are also reflected in the JSON schema in **[4]**.

